      • search

        public MetricsSet search(boolean usePaged,
                String queryText,
                String[] fields,
                int maxrows,
                Calendar earliestDate,
                Calendar latestDate)
                  throws ModelRunCanceledException
        Leverage the caller to do a search; results are limited to the specified number of rows.
        Parameters:
        usePaged - True to use paged searching (via cursor, faster). False to use older brute force method of getting all results at once.
        queryText - Search text.
        fields - The fields to return. Fields must contain type suffix. See TagUtils.addDataType(). If null, all fields will be returned.
        maxrows - Max rows to return.
        earliestDate - Earliest allowed date for returned data (inclusive). Can be null indicating no limit.
        latestDate - Latest allowed date for returned data (inclusive). Can be null indicating no limit.
        Returns:
        Results as a set.
        Throws:
        ModelRunCanceledException

      • checksum

        public long checksum()
        Returns a unique value encompassing results to support unit testing. Base implementation encompasses (a) item keys (b) item String & numeric values and (c) display text. These elements should be adequate for most models but do not encompass addenda. Authors of models may choose to override this method to guarantee that return value encompasses critical model results not reflection in the base implementation (one example: the model produces an addendum to its result that contains meaningful information).
        Returns:
        unique checksum value for unit testing.
